Subject: Default install.sh BRANCH to "release" for nadia customers

Upstream's scripts/install.sh declares BRANCH="main" at line 73 as a
plain default (NOT the ${BRANCH:-main} env-override form). The
--branch <X> flag overrides at line ~102 via BRANCH="$2".

nadia's customer-facing tree lives on the long-lived `release` branch
(IU-FR-3, IU-FR-4): CI force-pushes the renamed dist/nadia/ there after
every successful release build. The public install one-liner

    curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nadicodeai/nadia/release/scripts/install.sh | bash

MUST therefore clone `release` (runnable renamed tree), not `main`
(workshop layout — upstream/, patches/, .shepherd/, NOT runnable as
a customer install).

Changing the default to "release" keeps the --branch arg-parsing
escape hatch intact: developers can still pass `--branch main`
explicitly to clone the workshop layout (documented use case in
.shepherd/install-update/spec.md § IU-FR-6 closing sentence).

Spec IU-FR-7, IU-AC-4 (see .shepherd/install-update/spec.md).
Plan M4.1 (see .shepherd/install-update/plan.md).

Index: .sync-workdir/scripts/install.sh
===================================================================
--- .sync-workdir.orig/scripts/install.sh
+++ .sync-workdir/scripts/install.sh
@@ -71,7 +71,7 @@ USE_VENV=true
 RUN_SETUP=true
 SKIP_BROWSER=false
 NO_SKILLS=false
-BRANCH="main"
+BRANCH="release"
 INSTALL_COMMIT=""
 ENSURE_DEPS=""
 POSTINSTALL_MODE=false
@@ -166,7 +166,7 @@ while [[ $# -gt 0 ]]; do
             echo "  --no-skills    Start with a blank slate — seed no bundled skills, and"
             echo "                   write \$HERMES_HOME/.no-bundled-skills so future"
             echo "                   'hermes update' runs never inject bundled skills either"
-            echo "  --branch NAME  Git branch to install (default: main)"
+            echo "  --branch NAME  Git branch to install (default: release)"
             echo "  --commit SHA   Pin checkout to a specific commit after clone/update"
             echo "  --manifest     Print desktop bootstrap stage manifest as JSON"
             echo "  --stage NAME   Run one desktop bootstrap stage"
